76561198005927154,Not Recommended,305840,27874403,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,Gath Memvar,"Shallow Space has a ton of absolutely fantastic ideas and concepts, and the obvious influences from Homeworld and Nexus are very present (The Angelwing has a look-alike as a ship class, and the 3D interface).  The problem, however, is this game needs more time to bake.  The UI needs a lot of work (which I understand they're working on, which is fantastic!), the sandbox elements are very confusing (Yes, I researched, but my google-fu came up mostly empty), and I couldn't figure out how to custom design my ships (yes, I found the wrench), though I admit it's possible overlooked something.  The tutorials are lacking beyond basic controls and ship types/weapons, with no information how to access the more advanced features, but I know this will get fleshed out in time.For now, I say skip, but I'm going to be watching this game.  There's a lot of potential here, and I really hope it gets the development time it deserves, and it looks like it will.On a technical note, when this game crashes, it crashes the most gracefully I've EVER seen a program crash.  It doesn't lock up.  It doesn't crash to desktop.  It goes to console, copies the error into your clipboard, and tells you how to exit.  As a software engineer, this is beautiful design."
